        "body": "## What does this PR fix?\r\n\r\nTwo bugs on the MarsRover (`/marsrover`) page:\r\n\r\n### Bug 1: Excessive blank space above section titles\r\nThe `.section_title` class in `App.css` had `border-top: 20dvh solid transparent` \r\nwhich created a massive invisible gap (20% of viewport height) above every \r\nsection heading sitewide. Replaced with `padding-top: 2rem` for consistent, \r\nreasonable spacing.\r\n\r\n### Bug 2: Wrong environment variable name for NASA API\r\n`MarsRover.jsx` was referencing `VITE_API_KEY` but the correct variable \r\nname is `VITE_NASA_API_KEY`, causing Mars rover images to fail silently.\r\n\r\n### Bug 3: Mars 3D model container had no height constraint\r\nAdded `style={{ height: '400px', width: '100%' }}` to the Mars 3D model \r\nwrapper div to prevent it from expanding beyond the viewport.\r\n\r\n## Files changed\r\n- `src/App.css` — fixed `.section_title` spacing\r\n- `src/pages/MarsRover/MarsRover.jsx` — fixed API key variable + model container\r\n- `src/pages/MarsRover/MarsRover.module.css` — fixed section title padding\r\n",
